# Common Mistake ⭐

Many students write:

```java
lastRight.right = rightChild;

return root;
```

This is **wrong**.

The deleted node (`root`) still remains in the tree.

The correct statement is:

```java
return root.left;
```

because the left subtree becomes the new root of the updated subtree.

